<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5964999>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. Distoventral (palmar) margins of propodus (palm) of pereopod 2 (cheliped): a—Victoriopisa nhatrangensis sp. nov., holotype ♀, ZMMU Mb-1217; b—Victoriopisa cangio sp. nov., holotype ♀, ZMMU Mb-1219." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5964999/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5964957>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. General view (habitus) and live coloration of the described representatives of the genus Victoriopisa Karaman & Barnard, 1979: a—Victoriopisa nhatrangensis sp. nov., habitus, paratype ♀♀, ZMMU Mb-1218; b—head of Victoriopisa nhatrangensis sp. nov., c—live coloration of Victoriopisa cangio sp. nov., holotype, ZMMU Mb-1219, ovigerous ♀." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5964957/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5964973>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Victoriopisa nhatrangensis sp. nov., ♀ (dissected) (LEMMI): a—accessory flagellum of antenna 1; b—antenna 2; c—same distal segment; d—chela of gnathopod 1; e—chela of gnathopod 2; f—urosomal segments; g—coupling hooks of uropod 2. Sacle 0.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5964973/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5964959>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Victoriopisa nhatrangensis sp. nov., holotype ♀, ZMMU Mb-1217 (a–f), paratype ♀, ZMMU Mb-1218 (g): a— antenna 1; b—accessory flagellum of antenna 1; c—antenna 2; d—gnathopod 1; e—distoventral palmar margin of chela of Gn2; f—gnathopod 2; g—distoventral palmar margin of chela of Gn2." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5964959/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5964963>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Victoriopisa nhatrangensis sp. nov., holotype ♀, ZMMU Mb-1217: a—labrum (upper lip); b—labium (lower lip); c—left mandible; d—same, incisor process and pars incisiva; e—right mandible; f—same, incisor process and pars incisiva; g—maxilla 1; h—distal margin of inner plate of maxilla 1; i—maxilla 2; j—maxilliped." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5964963/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5964965>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Victoriopisanhatrangensis sp. nov., holotype ♀, ZMMU Mb-1217: a—pereopod 3; b—dactylus of P3; c—pereopod 4; d—pereopod 5; e—dactylus of P5; f—pereopod 6; g—pereopod 7; h—dactylus of P7." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5964965/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5964969>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Victoriopisa nhatrangensis sp. nov., holotype ♀, ZMMU Mb-1217: a—epimeral plate 1; b—epimeral plate 2; c—epimeral plate 3; d—telson; e—pleopod 2; f—hooks of retinacula of pleopod 1; g—uropod 1; h, i—uropod 2; j– uropod 3." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5964969/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5964951>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. The map of distribution of freshly collected species and Victoriopisa ovata (Dan & Le, 2005) (above) as well as the characteristic biotope in the Cần Giớ Mangrove Biosphere Reserve (below), where crustaceans were sampled." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5964951/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5964983>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Victoriopisa cangio sp. nov., holotype ♀, ZMMU Mb-1219: a—labrum (upper lip); b—labium (lower lip); c—left mandible; d—same, incisor process and pars incisiva; e—right mandible; f—same, incisor process and pars incisiva; g—maxilla 1; h—distal margin of inner plate of maxilla 1; I—maxilla 2; j—maxilliped." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5964983/files/figure.png" ;
